petData.description:
Howdy I'm Wednesday. I was wandering outside by myself where I was found by some nice folks and brought to safety. Yeah, you're assuming it was a Wednesday, huh? Nope, they named me after Wednesday from the Addams Family -- ha, ha, fooled ya! Anyhoo, I'm a friendly, active girl always joking around like that, come meet me soon!







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Mario was named after Mario Andretti as from an early age, he and his fellow racer-named siblings (Danika and Pippa) love to jet around at top speed.  He is a sweet and energetic love bug who is full of kisses and is brimming with confidence.

Nikki was trapped and left in a cage x5 days with no food or water. When brought in, she had 4 little babies and surrogated 9 additional. Her mom skills are impeccable and she deserves a great new home of her own!

Hello, I'm Eleanor Rigby, a beautiful New Zealand White girl released from a medical testing facility. Up til now my life was spent in a laboratory but I'm eager to see what the big wide world has to offer and hope to find a forever home where I'll be cherished member of the family. 



I arrived with a group of 12 laboratory bunnies, collectively #TheBeatlesBunnies and named after favorite songs. Feel free to sing my song when we meet!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
Very friendly and perky kitty! She loves to cuddle and be pet and also to play! Ziggy was named after her ziggy zag shaped tail tip.
This little one is getting ready for the day he will be ready for adoption. www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hello new friends! Are you looking for a super sweet dog to love forever? I think you should choose me! I would make the greatest companion for a adventure, but I would also be happy right at home with you! I am great with dogs, and people too! I have lots of energy and love to give, so it would benefit me greatly to have lots of exercise. Who doesn't love a good walk with their best friend though? Take me home!

Izzy is FIV/ FELV negative and parasite-free.  She is a sweet girl who is very playful and independent,  She loves playing with toys and chasing small balls.   Izzy was rescued as a small kitten and found tangled up in vines. Izzy is a little over 3 month old and is playful, independent and a loving cat that also has a feisty side.  She was rescued, she was tangled up in weeds. A good samaritan was able to get her out of it.  She does well with other cats with a slow introduction, but she don't not mind getting all the attention to herself. She loves being pet and playing with fuzzy ball. She would do best in a household without any children.

Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are tiny little panthers who stalk toys and protect me from invading feathers and keep the soft mice at bay by swatting them under the couch.  I owe them my undying gratitude for ensuring my safety. They are sweet lapcats and generous with their kisses.  



Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are identical twins, I mean totally identical.  No one can tell them apart.  They are 2/3 of the Makaha Happy Meal and equally sweet and tasty.  They have sleek and silky coats and fly up the cat trees like squirrels.  But once they crash, they are down for the count.

Goose is about 5 month old as of 8/31/21. He can be a little skittish at first, but once he opens up, he is playful, energetic and cuddly. 

He is vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, Fiv/Felv negative, dewormed, littler trained and flea bathed.

Greetings, I'm Pearl and I'm a recent SaveABunny arrival but already a favorite of some of the volunteers (shh, don't tell the other bunnies) for how my ears perk up when they talk to me nicely -- I do love a good compliment!



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi, I'm Loki. I was about to be dumped in a park in San Francisco when a Good Samaritan saw what was happening and intervened. My rescuer talked to the person dumping me and persuaded them to hand me over instead of abandoning me. From there I made my way to SaveABunny.



It was clear I was neglected as I was very skinny and had an old injury -- what looks like a broken leg that was never attended to so it healed a bit crooked, but it doesn't bother me so the vet says just to monitor. I can't tell you how happy I am to be safe and cared for -- and I'm a girl ready to let bygones be bygones and look forward to finding a forever home.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hello, I'm Good Day Sunshine, a beautiful New Zealand White girl released from a medical testing facility. Up til now my life was spent in a laboratory but I'm eager to see what the big wide world has to offer and hope to find a forever home where I'll be cherished member of the family. 



I arrived with a group of 12 laboratory bunnies, collectively #TheBeatlesBunnies and named after favorite songs. Feel free to sing my song when we meet!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Dyson is a very finicky and dynamic kitty! He's got a crochetty "Mraaaooow" sound and LOVES wet food! He really likes time by himself as he observes the humans of the house. Dyson gets a kick out of laser pointing and his favorite treat is temptation or bacon bits! He likes to be pet, but not picked up much. His eyes are BRIGHT BLUE! He loves to find the warm rays of sunshine and bask in them on the floor. Someone with patience will be needed, but his warmth, love and generous petting will be so worth it!

General Pebbles is highly curious and adventuresome. He is mechanically minded and studies all the new toys and marvels at the workings of water fountains with avid interest and concentration. He is an affectionate lap cat and generous with his kisses.

This is one Lab who you can still teach new tricks! I came to Kauai Humane Society as a stray, so the staff isn't sure what my home life was like before I came here. However, they have learned that I LOVE TO LEARN - and treats motivate me to learn all sorts of tricks! I sit and give good eye contact and have learned to walk better on leash all through treats and calm, consistent training.

That's what I would like in my new home - calm, consistent training (and some treats). :-)

I can be initially slow to warm up to people and prone to escape if not handled securely; hence why that consistent training and treats is so important. ;-) And within a day or so, I will warm up and learn my routine so fast!

I have met some dogs I was a little unsure about, and other easy-going, very social puppies that I have done great with. The key to my heart, and to being my best-matched home, is understanding I might start out needing more patience and initial routine than your average pet. Watching me learn and grow is so rewarding!

Rudy is a very sweet boy! He may seem angry when you greet him at his kennel but once you get in his kennel with him and love on him or play with him in the yard he is a total lap dog! Rudy was surrendered to us because their owners are moving to the mainland and couldn't take him with them. Ask us about our boy Rudy! Take him home today!

Hello, I'm Quimby and I'm a handsome young boy. Don't you like the butterfly I carry around on my nose? We like playing together, dancing and flying!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
This little fella has a bullseye on his eye. Came with sibling Carmelita from a rescue. Apply for Bullseye at www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

Princess is a prissy princess. She LOVES to be pet softly down her back from head to tail. She doesnt like to be carried around that much, but she wants to be right by your side the whole day! Her eyes are brilliant and she enjoys watching your every move you make. Favorite food is Gravy Lovers from Fancy Feast and favorite toy is a feather wand and of course that laser light! Although she always follows her humans around, she also has a wonderful independent streak where she loves to explore. Favorite nap spot is high up on the top of the cat tree overseeing the house.

Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are tiny little panthers who stalk toys and protect me from invading feathers and keep the soft mice at bay by swatting them under the couch.  I owe them my undying gratitude for ensuring my safety. They are sweet lapcats and generous with their kisses.  



Miss Burger and Miss McFlurry are identical twins, I mean totally identical.  No one can tell them apart.  They are 2/3 of the Makaha Happy Meal and equally sweet and tasty.  They have sleek and silky coats and fly up the cat trees like squirrels.  But once they crash, they are down for the count.

Linus is a gentle and affectionate lap cat who is rather chatty about his adventures.  He likes to keep tabs on his humans and is either in their laps or close by. Linus enjoys his toys and cannot resist anything that dangles, has feathers, or jingles with a bell, and revels in a rousing game of chase with his twin sister Lucy.

Hello I'm Maisie and I'm a fabulous friendly girl. I arrived at SaveABunny as a baby with a heart murmur, but have grown big and strong -- you should see my binkies! 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Ghost is a Flame Point Siamese boy, who came from a homeless camp where he was cared for by a woman who wanted him to have a happy, easy life. He is a charming lap cat with a calm disposition and a very impressive purr! Ghost will only be adopted as a pair with one of his siblings, Pumpkin or Tricks.

Hola, mi nombre es Cuervo, and I'm named after a tequila -- I'm a teetotaler who sticks strictly to water, but I like my name anyways cuz it's fun to say out loud. My favorite thing to do is stand up! 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
Baby was found in Kapolei next to the deceased mother. Saved by a locksmith and surrendered to Lucky Paws. Adopt at www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

chance was rescued from an area near Kapahulu Ave and Ekela. He was a frequent guest at an apartment complex where the security did not approve of him coming into the building. Hes nervous at first but is kind, gentle, and soft. He likes to be held and he enjoys chin skritches! This guy deserves all the best after being stuck outdoors for so long. Please fill out an application for Chance at www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt
Bernadette is looking for a lovely family to call her home. If you're interested to adopt Bernadette, please visit our website oahuspca.org and fill up the adoption application.

This little nugget was found on the road of Kaneohe marine corps base by some visitors to the island. They took good care of him, took him on adventures, and called Lucky Paws to help before they depart Oahu. This kitty is a top gem. Very social already and likes dogs and cats alike thus far. has lots of energy.

Hello I'm Lovebug, a friendly girl who always wants to help with whatever you're doing and be involved with everything that's going on. A real busybody!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Monica is a sweet, young rabbit who has spent her formative months in a foster home and is ready to find a forever home of her own! She is a bit sensitive, so a quieter home would be great for her. But once she settles in, she is an engaging rabbit that will make an awesome companion. 



All Humane Society of Sonoma County rabbits are companion house rabbits. They live indoors only and cage free- living in a pen or free-roam in the home. This lets them live much longer, happier lives! Indoor rabbits can live 12+ years and require a lot of time and commitment. In return they offer years of love and companionship! Primary Color: Grey Weight: 3.48kg Age: 0yrs 6mths 3wks Animal has been Spayed
Bucky O'Hare is shy young bunny who would prefer a quiet, loving home. However, once he gets comfortable he is very outgoing and curious!

This little girl was found with sibling Bullseye. Both had terrible ringworm which is being treated. The ringworm makes for a terrible picture but she will be a beautiful white and orange kitty when healed.

Princess is a dynamic kitty! She loves the head to tail petting! She has the cutest meows and arches up her back when you touch her. She likes to attack anything that has strings or tassels and is playful. She absolutely goes nuts for shredded chicken and tuna juice is her jam! Dontcha just love her fluffy white chest?! Shes very bonded with her sister, Princess.

Hi I'm Parchment, if you need me for anything just call and I'll hop right on over! 



I was just a couple weeks old when I came here with my mom Cotton Candy and my sibs, part of a confiscation of 29 bunnies by authorities due to extreme neglect. Mom was so brave protecting all of us and we grew up healthy and thriving and now I'm ready to experience everything life has to offer.



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

petData.breed: Irish Terrier & American Staffordshire Terrier Mix

petData.description: Marv is a playful boy who loves all the pets in the world! Marv was a rescue we picked up, along with his brother Harry,  around the Dole Plantation. They are both so loving and can be clingy, but who doesn't love that?! Harry and Marv have been strays their whole life so it will take time to adjust to a home setting. They have settled in very nicely with us, they are pleasant on the leash and very friendly. Ask us more about the dynamic duo and adopt Marv today or both of the brothers!

Hello, I'm Oslo, I'm an older Californian boy and this is Maris (white lop), my hot young girlfriend. We were adopted a while ago then returned when our human could not take care of us any more, but look forward to creating a new future together.



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Macaroni!!!! He had an accessed back and couldn't walk well! Rescued by members of Catopia Hawaii, then we fostered him back to health! Macaroni is his name because his back had a bend like a macaroni noodle. Macaroni loves to observe. Hes often scared of new surroundings, but adjusts in due time. He love to seek out companionship with other kitties. Hes alsways got a look of great concern on his face, but thats just his RBF.
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Soni was rescued from the harbor in Haleiwa and was an obvious dump. The caretaker contacted us and we went up to retrieve her. The caretaker though she was so beautiful so she got fixed and chipped and is now looking for her forever home!

Hello I'm Honeybun, a friendly girl who always wants to help with whatever you're doing and be involved with everything that's going on. A real busybody!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi there, I'm Bam Bam and I'm a teeny tiny little guy -- I'm may struggle to tip the scales at 2 lbs, but I'm packed with personality and have big, big plans to rule the world!







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Good day, I'm Harley, a simply gorgeous harlequin bunny. I'm a middle-aged girl who was adopted then returned after a number of years after my human could no longer care for me, but with age comes wisdom and I know life still has plenty to offer. I'm very calm and gentle and melt when petted and am ready for my next chapter.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi I'm a young, cute lion head boy. I don't roar though, I'd rather play then settle down for a nice cuddle and nap and maybe a nice head rub.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

I want a partner who lives in the slow-lane -- someone who sits a lot and enjoys having a warm, soft bunny lounging side-by-side. In our Bunny Zen zone we can: post photos of the two of us snuggling and make everyone jealous; sing our favorite tunes; watch silly videos of bunnies snuggling; stare out the window and blissfully mind-wander; share our forever love. I'm shy and would appreciate a quiet companion who will help me become all I am capable of becoming. P.S. Are salads on the menu twice a day? I'll come happily hopping. Not shy about that!



All Humane Society of Sonoma County rabbits are companion house rabbits. They live indoors only and cage free- living in a pen or free-roam in the home. This lets them live much longer, happier lives! Indoor rabbits can live 12+ years and require a lot of time and commitment. In return they offer years of love and companionship! Primary Color: Tortoiseshell Weight: 3.37kg Age: 4yrs 9mths 0wks Animal has been Spayed

This was part of a litter who was rescued from Sonny's Auto at Sand Island. Mama was missing and babies were in a bad place. Flashy is FAST! She loves to play and dart around the cage. She enjoys wrestling the siblings, eating slurry, and taking long naps. Very cuddly and loves to sleep near your head. She is just a little kitty but shes a BIG treasure! Shes VERY cottonball-like and is calico. Mostly Grey, legs white, orange stripe on face. Very cool!

Elvis is a fun loving goofy boy! He loves to play in the yard with lots of toys and can keep himself entertained. He has a lot of energy and needs a strong handler, sometimes he doesn't know how big he actually is! Adopt Elvis today you will never be bored with him!

Hello, I'm Peach and I'm a girl who is a little withdrawn, so I'm staying in a foster home to receive special attention and one-on-one time to heal my past trauma and learn how to trust.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

McNugget was found living under a McDonalds Dumpster in mililani. He was just a kitten and was by himself with no colony nearby. He was adopted, but then released to the wild where he was recaptured and then turned into HHS. Because he was microchipped, we got a call to pick him up and now he is prepped for a new adventure. Hes very sweet. LOVES to be pet, but doesnt like to be held until he gets to know you. Hes playful like a kitten. He likes dogs and other cats just fine! He loves naps and pushes his nose into you every night demanding affection! Top notch kitty!

petData.breed: Pit Bull Terrier & Labrador Retriever Mix
petData.description: Smart boy Miloh loves learning new things and enjoys showing off his obedience skills! Call 808-754-1519 to learn more about Miloh.

Furikake is a fun and energetic kitten, loves to play with his sister (Nori, also available for adoption). He was born with a bent tail, but it does not bother him or prevent him from living his best life. He is outgoing and adjust to new environment quickly. His favorite toys are laser pointers, cat teaser toys and fuzzy ball. 



He is flea bathed, neutered, microchipped, vaccinated
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
Pringle was abandoned by his previous family, but is looking for a new one! Sweet and cuddly, Pringle will likely snuggle with you in bed. He also loves chatting!

Bellatrix (Bella) is a beautiful Siamese kitty who was rescued from the Ranch 99 in Moanalua after a security guard witnessed her be dumped out of a van by her former owner. She recently had three babies, but will be spayed and ready to go to her forever home in mid October when she is done nursing. Bella is extremely affectionate and loves to be around people, especially calm children. She isn't shy about letting you know when she wants pets! She would do well being adopted with her kitten (Ginny), or as an only cat, or possibly into a home with other cats after a proper slow introduction. She is an excellent mother who deserves to be spoiled by her very own forever family after she's done raising her kittens.
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Boris the Blade is a battle hardened street cat who got socialized by humans and is now living the good life! An A-1 nap-master deserves a an absolutely chill environment where he can lounge and be spoiled. He's had all of his teeth removed so he drools a bit.. which we find endearing. Loves kittens, loves wet food. Slightly hard of hearing, and slightly hard of seeing but really enjoys staying indoors and finding the softest spot in the house.

Good morning I'm Bettina, a beautiful blue eyed girl who just arrived. Am still a little shy and getting to know everyone but soon my dutchie 'tude will start to shine through -- and you should see me binky and dance when I'm out to play!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Pumpkin is a light ginger little girl, who has been very loved by humans from the beginning of her life. She was cared for by a homeless woman who realized she could not provide the life she wanted this sweet girl to have. Pumpkin's motto is play hard, nap harder. If you sit down around her, be prepared for her to climb into your lap immediately, it's her favorite place to be! Pumpkin would like to be adopted with one of her brothers, Tricks or Ghost, or by a family who already has a young kitty for her to play with.
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi I'm Henry Huggins and I'm a young boy who's just an all-around nice guy just like the character I'm named after from the ""Beezus and Ramona"" books by children's author Beverly Cleary.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Justin is a super sweet and SUPER soft male rex rabbit ready and waiting for a new home! He would make a great companion for anyone ready to take on life with a house rabbit. Justin and Lance are brothers and wouldn't mind going home together. 



All Humane Society of Sonoma County rabbits are companion house rabbits. They live indoors only and cage free- living in a pen or free-roam in the home. This lets them live much longer, happier lives! Indoor rabbits can live 12+ years and require a lot of time and commitment. In return they offer years of love and companionship! Primary Color: White Secondary Color: Black Weight: 2.2kg Age: 1yrs 1mths 2wks Animal has been Neutered

Tricks is a dark ginger tabby boy, who was cared for from an early age by a homeless woman who wanted a better life for him. He is very sweet and cuddly, but has a high energy playful side as well. Tricks would love to be adopted with one of his siblings, Ghost or Pumpkin, or by a family who already has a kitten his age for him to play with. Maybe his next trick could be stealing your heart?

Maverick is about 5 months old as of 8/3/21. He can be a little skittish when you first meet him, but once he opens up, he is very energetic and playful. 



He is vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, Fiv/Felv negative, dewormed, littler trained and flea bathed.

This kitty was all alone in a gutter in Waipahu. The street was busy and dangerous and a concerned citizen called us. She is sweet and likes to march in place and arch her back as you pet her. What a great kitten!

Zelda is a very sweet girl! She loves to play with her toys and would thrive as the only dog in the house hold. Zelda has been in foster for sometime now so we are not sure how she is with other kids, since the foster does not have any kids. Zelda does like to rough house play so she would benefit from a strong handler. Ask us more about Zelda today and take her home!

Hi I'm Paperback, a young girl who jumps out of bed in the morning to eagerly greet the day -- I'm friendly and interactive, too! 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Zelda has magical powers and seems to have a  calming effect on all creatures around her.  She is very mellow and an affectionate lap cat and was the first of her litter to win over the family dog.  She now has him well trained.

Larry and Blanca are two peas in a pod, and they enjoy sharing a big salad every day! These two house buns are very much in love and are looking to find a home together. Larry is inquisitive and likes to see what you're up to. Blanca is well mannered and laid back. Larry and Blanca are experienced house rabbits with years of indoor house-living under their belts. They have lived with older children in the past. They would make a great pair for anyone prepared for the joys of bunny companionship! Call our Healdsburg campus at 707-431-3386 to find out more about this soft and sweet duo. 

 





All Humane Society of Sonoma County rabbits are companion house rabbits. They live indoors only and cage free- living in a pen or free-roam in the home. This lets them live much longer, happier lives! Indoor rabbits can live 12+ years and require a lot of time and commitment. In return they offer years of love and companionship! Primary Color: White Weight: 2.2kg Age: 4yrs 0mths 1wks Animal has been Spayed
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

This Russian beauty was rescued while pregnant and soon delivered a healthy litter of 4 kittens on July 19, 2021.  She was an attentive, loving, and patient mom.  She is as sweet as she is beautiful.  Natalya is a young adult and is estimated to be less than a year old.

Are you looking for an outdoor adventurer? Look no further! I would be the greatest friend for a nice hike, or even a day playing on the beach. I am a great companion for other dogs, and people too! If you take me home, I will try to be the goodest boy ever! I can't wait to find my forever family!

Hallo, I'm Halo, a young boy still growing into my ears. They flap all over the place, creating quite a nice cooling breeze! 



Here's me when I was a bit younger. 







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Cloud was a mama outdoor cat who's babies were in a dangerous area. Cloud and her babies were brought in to safety and to be raised by a foster home. Cloud is a sweet and mild kitty cat. She likes to watch the room from afar and she will chatter at birds in the window. We are actively working to socialize Cloud better. Shes timid, but sweet n cuddly too! She likes dogs and other cats but does not like kids so much.

Morocco is an 8yr old sweet loving cat. He was rehomed by his original owner for about a year, but he was unfortunately neglected by them and was returned to his original owner. When he returned, he was over weight and had matted furr. He is currently on a special diet for his urinary crystals and to bring his weight down. His original owner can no longer keep him due to health issues, so we are looking for someone who is willing to give him a loving furever home.

Ka'eo is living his best life in his foster home! His very sweet fosters are not able to adopt him because they will be moving off the island soon. We would love for him to find his forever home where he can retire so he doesn't have to come back to the shelter! He is very sweet, we picked him up a few months back at Hawaiian Humane Society all skin and bones. We fed him and gave him all the love and more! He looks so good now and relaxing in his foster home. If you are interested in senior dogs and giving them their forever home, contact us today! Mahalo.

Aloha! My name is Sir Wallace and I am the sweetest boy around. When I arrived at the shelter, I was pretty sick and in bad shape, but the staff saved me and got me into a foster home. I am now healthy, flourishing, and ready for my forever home. I love playing with my older dog siblings and especially love my cat sibling. Foster reports that Sir Wallace is super smart, picked up walking on a leash, and house training quickly. He is good with kids, cats, and other dogs. Despite his unlucky beginnings, he is a trusting, loving, and outgoing pup now. Give this perfect pup a home!

Hello there I'm Blush, and I'm a very pretty girl with charm to spare. But because my ears are kind of fancy I need my human guardian to pay close attention and help me clean them frequently so they don't become gunked up and infected. 







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hello we're Vienna (brown) and Silvio (black lop) an older couple who love each other very much and would thrive a quiet home with gentle humans. 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Adi is coming up on 4 months of age, spayed, vaccinated, and full of sweet kitten love. She has buckets of confidence, loves to play, is very curious and affectionate, is a snuggle thief, and even enjoys meeting new people to obtain extra scratches. If you find yourself with an oversupply of unused heartstrings, fingers ready for scratching, and a purr deficit - we can hook you up.

Hina is as lovable a gal as they come!  She adores humans, can get rambunctious and mouthy so not a good fit for kids.  She is happy going on a couple leisurely walks a day and snoozing in between.  Hina would thrive as the only dog with humans who are savvy to the bully breeds.  She is strong, but never malicious with her exuberance.  We have had Hina in our care for several years and would love to see her find a home of her own where she is queen.  She is currently on the island of Kauai, with travel of bully breeds becoming increasingly restrictive, we understand it will be a challenge to get her to the mainland.  However, we are open to homes within the state of Hawaii.

Oh hi there, I'm Tinsel (silver) and this is Roxy (white). I'm a friendly and people-loving middle-aged girl adopted from SaveABunny a while back. Roxy became my BFF gal pal a couple years ago. We're back here because our guardians moved out of the country and were not able to take us with them. We're children friendly and hope to find a home soon!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Larry and Blanca are two peas in a pod, and they enjoy sharing a big salad every day! These two house buns are very much in love and are looking to find a home together. Larry is inquisitive and likes to see what you're up to. Blanca is well mannered and laid back. Larry and Blanca are experienced house rabbits with years of indoor house-living under their belts. They have lived with older children in the past. They would make a great pair for anyone prepared for the joys of bunny companionship!
